      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GILLENBAH TIGER (5) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a slick early split, holding on for a minor placing when third and beaten 6 lengths at this track over 520m in 30.36. Deserves serious consideration. BIG BANG BUSTER (1) was below best last time but prior to that was narrowly beaten when fourth (30.44) in a Mix 3/4 at this track. Can feature with the right run. I'LL SEE (8) should enjoy clear running from the outside box. Below best latest at this track (30.64) when 6th and beaten 14 lengths. Form here at this distance is strong including one wins. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from six starts. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. SAINT RICO (7) is always a threat when he races at this journey.",
